OL,3,CSir Keir to face pressure from MPs to
OL,4,Cscrap two-child benefit cap
OL,6,FSNP Westminster Leader Stephen Flynn
OL,7,FMP said: "Keir Starmer must not fail
OL,8,Fhis first major test in government by
OL,9,Frefusing to scrap the cap. It is the
OL,10,Fbare minimum required to tackle child
OL,11,Fpoverty ` and to begin to deliver the
OL,12,Fchange that people in Scotland were
OL,13,Fpromised.
OL,15,F"Labour MPs have a choice today. They
OL,16,Fcan lift children out of poverty by
OL,17,Fvoting for the SNP amendment to
OL,18,Fabolish the cap ` or they will push
OL,19,Fchildren into poverty by keeping it in
OL,20,Fplace.
