OL,3,CSir Keir to face pressure from MPs to
OL,4,Cscrap two-child benefit cap
OL,6,FAgainst the background of rising child
OL,7,Fpoverty ` with more than four million
OL,8,Fchildren now living in low-income
OL,9,Fhouseholds ` the Prime Minister has
OL,10,Fbeen urged by charities, opposition
OL,11,Fparties and some of his own MPs to
OL,12,Fabolish the limit.
OL,14,FThe Prime Minister has so far
OL,15,Fsuggested the state of the public
OL,16,Ffinances means they cannot afford to
OL,17,Faxe the benefit limit unless economic
OL,18,Fgrowth is secured first.
